data.content:
noun
or yadda yadda /ˈjɑːdəˈjɑːdə/ or yada yada yada or yadda yadda yadda /ˈjɑːdəˈjɑːdəˈjɑːdə/
[noncount] US informal :talk or language that is boring or that offers little information
They had to listen to the usual yada yada about bike safety. - often used as an interjection in place of words that are very dull or not worth saying
It was your typical day: I went to work, came home, had dinner, yada yada yada.
